"agent\": \"agent_2\", \"vote\": \"Candidate A\"}", "thoughts": "We have gathered that no info on D teamwork/communication. Now need to evaluate candidates based on known attributes.\n\nList attributes:\n\nCandidate A:\n- can anticipate dangerous situations (good for safety)\n- able to see complex connections (cognitive)\n- excellent spatial vision (important for navigation)\n- very good leadership qualities (teamwork)\n- regarded as a show-off (negative perception)\n- regarded as not open to new ideas (rigidity)\n\nCandidate B:\n- very conscientious (reliability)\n- handles stress very well (pressure)\n- good at assessing weather conditions (technical)\n- excellent computer skills (technical)\n- relatively weak memory for numbers (potential issue)\n- makes nasty remarks about colleagues (teamwork/communication negative)\n\nCandidate C:\n- can make correct decisions quickly (decision-making)\n- difficulty communicating ideas (teamwork)\n- regarded as egocentric (teamwork)\n- not very willing to further his education (development)\n- keeps calm in a crisis (pressure)\n- understands complicated technology (technical)\n\nCandidate D:\n- responds to unexpected events adequately (adaptability)\n- can concentrate very well (cognitive)\n- solves problems extremely well (technical)\n- takes responsibility seriously (reliability)\n- regarded as a know-it-all (perception)\n- has a hot temper (teamwork/pressure)\n- no info on teamwork/communication\n\nWe need to weigh strengths vs weaknesses for long-distance pilot. Key criteria: reliability, technical competence, calm under pressure, decision-making, teamwork/communication, professional development.\n\nAssess each:\n\nA: strong technical and situational awareness, leadership, but show-off and not open to new ideas could affect crew relations and adaptability. No explicit stress handling but leadership suggests good.\n\nB: conscientious, stress handling, weather assessment, computer skills good. Weakness: weak memory for numbers (could affect navigation), nasty remarks (bad teamwork). Overall maybe okay but teamwork issue.\n\nC: quick correct decisions, calm in crisis, tech understanding good. Weaknesses: communication difficulty, egocentric, unwilling to further education (development). Teamwork issues.\n\nD: strong problem solving, concentration, responsibility, handles unexpected events. Weaknesses: hot temper, know-it-all, possibly poor teamwork (loner). No info on communication.\n\nWe need best overall. Likely candidate A has strong technical and leadership, but show-off and closed to new ideas could be problematic but maybe manageable. Candidate B has interpersonal negativity. Candidate C has egocentric and communication issues. Candidate D has temper and know-it-all, also no teamwork info.\n\nThus A seems strongest despite some negatives. I'd vote Candidate A.\n\nNow produce output."}
